  "day": 65,
  "key": "day_65_the_risen_messiah",
  "version": 1,
  "updated_at": "2026-02-17",
  "title": {
    "en": "He Is Risen"
  },
  "intro": {
    "en": ["The women hurried from the tomb,", "afraid yet filled with joy."]
  },
  "blocks": {
    "en": [
      {
        "type": "text",
        "marker": "appearance",
        "icon": "wb_sunny",
        "label": { "en": "Jesus Met Them" },
        "lines": [
          "Suddenly Jesus met them.",
          "“Greetings,” he said.",
          "They came to him,",
          "clasped his feet,",
          "and worshiped him."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "marker": "reassurance",
        "icon": "favorite",
        "label": { "en": "Do Not Be Afraid" },
        "lines": [
          "Jesus said to them,",
          "“Do not be afraid.",
          "Go and tell my brothers",
          "to go to Galilee;",
          "there they will see me.”"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "marker": "relationship",
        "icon": "groups",
        "label": { "en": "My Father and Your Father" },
        "lines": [
          "He said,",
          "“I am returning to my Father and your Father,",
          "to my God and your God.”"
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
  "question": {
    "en": "The women worshiped him. Why do you think they responded this way? What does the resurrection suggest about everything Jesus had said before?"
  },
  "further_reading": {
    "en": ["Matthew 28:8–10", "John 20:16–18"]
  }
}
